@wiseguy20  

Whether a copy of a spell is countered depends on how it was played - more specifically, whether it was cast or not. [Mirari](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Mirari) or [Twincast](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Twincast), for example, simply puts a copy on the stack. The chalice's ability will trigger when the original is cast, but not when it is copied (although note that if X = 2 then it will also be triggered by casting twincast/reverberate itself). [Isochron Scepter](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Isochron Scepter) and [Panoptic Mirror](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Panoptic Mirror), although they also "make a copy" of a spell, actually cast that spell, so that will trigger the chalice.  

How you cast a spell has no bearing on its converted mana cost, which will always be the same number for that spell. [Force of Will](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Force of Will)'s CMC will always be 5, even though no one will ever hardcast that.

@Banjo: Actually, this thing is way more useful in shutting down TES/TPS. Affinity don't have much of a CMC focus. Much. CMC 2 could make it painful, especially if they opted to run [Naturalize](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Naturalize) over [Krosan Grip](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Krosan Grip) or [Nature's Claim](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Nature's Claim). That does happen to shut down [Arcbound Ravager](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Arcbound Ravager), [Stoneforge Mystic](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Stoneforge Mystic), [Fling](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Fling), [Ethersworn Canonist](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Ethersworn Canonist), and [Vault Skirge](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Vault Skirge). Not a bad spread, considering those are pretty key, regardless of which Affinity variant they run.  
I also like this against Landstill, set it to 2 to kill card advantage. Sure, there are issues getting it out and keeping it out, but time bought is time well spent.   

Anyways, really math card. Love the filling outta this donut, man. 5/5
